1-  A User can only have 1 role whether it's a Bank Personnel, Loan Provider or Loan Customer
2- A Bank Personnel user can approve/reject loan applications. 
3- A Bank Personnel user can approve/reject loan fund applications. 
4- Loans are added by Bank Personnel users by specifying loan min_amount, max_amount, interest_rate and duration which is in number of months. 
5- A Bank Personnel who adds a Loan is added to the database as bank_personnel.
6- A Loan Customer can apply for a Loan Application by specifying a Loan Object and an amount. 
7- A Loan Provider can apply for a Loan Fund Application by specifying a certain amount. 
8- A Bank Personnel user who approves/rejects loan applications is saved to the application in the database as bank_personnel.  
9- A Bank Personnel user who approves/rejects loan fund applications is saved to the application in the database as bank_personnel. 
10- A Loan Customer who applies for a Loan Application is saved to the application in the database as customer.
11- A Loan Provider who applies for a Loan Fund Application is saved to the application in the database as customer.
12- A Loan cannot be edited once added by a Bank Personnel. 
13- A Role Can only be 1 of 3 values [Loan Provider, Loan Customer, Bank Personnel]
14- For a user to sign up he must provide username, email, password and role. 
